= Usd Stitch Export =
#context: sop
#type: node

"""Exports SOP geometry to a per-frame USD sequence and stitches it into a USD value clip."""

== Overview ==

Usd Stitch Export wraps a USD ROP and a USD Stitch Clips ROP into a single SOP, running in two steps. __Save to Disk__ writes the incoming SOP geometry to one USD file per frame. __Render__ then stitches the per-frame files into a USD value clip set, so the whole sequence can be referenced as a single animated asset.

@parameters

Load from Disk:
    #id: loadfromdisk
    Reads the geometry back from the exported USD sequence (USD Sequence Path) instead of cooking the input. Errors if the sequence has not been exported yet.

Import Path Prefix:
    #id: pathprefix
    USD scope the geometry is imported under. Default: `/Geometry`.

Sample Frame:
    #id: sampleframe
    Frame at which the geometry is sampled. Default: `$F`.

Flush Data After Each Frame:
    #id: fileperframe
    Flushes data to disk after every frame to limit memory use.

Track Primitive Existence to Set Visibility:
    #id: trackprimexistence
    Toggles primitive visibility based on whether it exists on each frame.

Base Name:
    #id: basename
    Base name of the exported USD files. Default: `$HIPNAME.$OS`.

Base Folder:
    #id: basedir
    Output directory for the exported files. Default: `$HIP/geo`.

Version:
    #id: version
    Version number of the exported sequence.

Start/End/Inc:
    #id: f
    Frame range and increment to export.

Save to Disk:
    #id: execute
    Exports the per-frame USD sequence.

Sync Version:
    #id: sync_version
    Keeps the clip version in sync with the export Version. Disable to set the clip version independently.

Clip Version:
    #id: clip_version
    Version of the stitched value clip, used when Sync Version is off.

Time Codes per Second:
    #id: tcps
    Time codes per second written into the value clip. Default: `$FPS`.

Render:
    #id: execute2
    Stitches the exported sequence into a USD value clip. Reports an error if any frame in the range is missing or cannot be opened.

USD Sequence Path:
    #id: usd_seq_path
    Path template of the exported per-frame USD sequence (mirrors the Save to Disk output, with `$F` substituted per frame).

USD Stitch Path:
    #id: usd_stitch_path
    Output path of the stitched value clip (mirrors the Render output template).
